elements.name: Accessible: friendly and easy to talk to; approachable.
elements.title: ACCESSIBLE: friendly and easy to talk to; approachable.

elements.name: question1
elements.title: ADVENTUROUS: willing to take risks or try out new methods, ideas, or experiences.

elements.name: question2
elements.title: AUTHORITATIVE: commanding and self-confident; likely to be respected and obeyed.

elements.name: question3
elements.title: CAPABLE: having power and ability; efficient; competent.

elements.name: question4
elements.title: CASUAL: relaxed and unconcerned; informal.

elements.name: question5
elements.title: COURAGEOUS: not deterred by danger or risk; brave.

elements.name: question6
elements.title: DARING: adventurous or audaciously bold.

elements.name: question7
elements.title: ENCHANTING: delightfully charming or attractive.

elements.name: question8
elements.title: ENLIGHTENED: having or showing a rational, modern, and well-informed outlook.

elements.name: question9
elements.title: FUN: amusing, entertaining, or enjoyable.

elements.name: question10
elements.title: HAPPY: delighted, pleased, or glad.

elements.name: question11
elements.title: HELPFUL: giving or ready to give aid or assistance.

elements.name: question12
elements.title: IMAGINATIVE: having or showing creativity or inventiveness.

elements.name: question13
elements.title: INTELLIGENT: having good understanding or a high capacity; quick to comprehend.

elements.name: question14
elements.title: INTIMATE: closely acquainted; personal, close.

elements.name: question15
elements.title: INVENTIVE: having the ability to create or design new things or to think originally.

elements.name: question16
elements.title: LIVELY: full of life and energy; active and outgoing.

elements.name: question17
elements.title: PROTECTIVE: having or showing a strong wish to keep someone or something safe.

elements.name: question18
elements.title: PROVOCATIVE: arousing desire or interest deliberately. (Not necessarily sexual)

elements.name: question19
elements.title: SKILLED: having or showing the knowledge, ability, or training to perform certain activities.

elements.name: question20
elements.title: REBELLIOUS: showing a desire to resist authority, control, or convention.

elements.name: question21
elements.title: REVOLUTIONARY: radically new or innovative; outside or beyond established procedure, principles, etc.

elements.name: question22
elements.title: VIRTUOUS: free from moral wrong; pure and wholesome.

elements.name: question23
elements.title: VISIONARY: thinking about or planning the future with imagination or wisdom.
